PETALING JAYA: Malaysia Airlines will only fly family members to Perth if any physical wreckage found is authoritatively confirmed to be that from flight MH370.Its chief executive officer Ahmad Jauhari Yahya said on Sunday that arrangements would be made as soon as the relevant government agencies provide MAS clearance to bring family members to the site where any potential wreckage is kept."A Family Assistance Centre (FAC) will be established in Perth. The FAC will become the focal point for all activities that have been planned for the families including briefings, religious and prayer services," he said in a statement.Ahmad Jauhari also reiterated the airlineâ€™s commitment and support from relevant foreign Governments which continue to search for the aircraft.In addition to its continued cooperation with all authorities involved in the investigation, the national carrier also continues to provide welfare and support to the families of the passengers.